President Obama announced the appointment of three individuals to the National Council on Federal Labor-Management Relations. Michael B. Filler, the Director of the Public Services Division of the International Brotherhood of Teamsters, was reappointed to the Council. David J. Holway, the President of the National Association of Government Employees and the International Brotherhood of Police Officers, was also reappointed. H.T. Nguyen, the Executive Director/General Counsel of the Federal Education Association, was reappointed as well. The Council, created in 2009, advises the President on labor-management relations in the executive branch and is co-chaired by the Director of the Office of Personnel Management and the Deputy Director for Management of the Office of Management and Budget. The President also designated several Deputy Secretaries to be members of the Council.